<recipe>
    <name>Smith Family Lasagna</name>
    <indexCharacter>S</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Cut sweet onions into sections, then dice in food processor
2. Mince the garlic cloves
3. Saute onions and minced garlic in olive oil in large pan until onions are glazed
4. Add Italian Sausage to pan and cook until done
5. Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste and Italian seasoning to pan
6. Simmer until flavors are mixed, or simmer on low in a crock pot
7. Grate the mozzarella cheese withe a box grater
8. Cook the lasagna in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes (check box directions)
9. Put a small amount of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 9” x 13” pyrex pan
10. Layer the lasagna into the pyrex pan in three layers in the following order: noodles, spaghetti sauce, ricotta, mozzarella and  parmesan 
11. Bake covered in a 350-degree oven for 25 minutes
12. Remove foil and bake for an additional 20 minutes
Note: Baking instructions may not be exactly correct
</instructions>
